{
  "number": 974,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/974",
  "title": "[pagination]: Disabled links can still be clicked",
  "body": "The way we _disable_ pagination links currently is by adding a CSS class to them, and make them look greyed out. But in the DOM, they are still links and can be followed, leading the user to a page with no results.\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/14426396/f6f97992-ffee-11e5-8aee-8b6883e570d6.png)\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/14426404/023f536c-ffef-11e5-887e-ec5ca9cd8795.png)\n\nI suggest we replace the `a` with `span` when they are disabled.\n",
  "created_at": "2016-04-11T12:10:15Z",
